I"[<p><a href="https://github.com/thecdil/bootstrap-template">bootstrap-template</a> is a basic template repository to create a <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/">Bootstrap</a> site using Jekyll on GitHub Pages (or where every you want to host it). 
The layout is based on the <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/examples/">Bootstrap starter template example</a> with a navbar, search box (using lunr.js), and sticky footer.
It is intended as a quick starting point for creating new web projects.</p>

<p>The basic steps for using bootstrap-template are:</p>

<ol>
  <li>create repository from the template</li>
  <li>edit _config.yml</li>
  <li>edit content pages</li>
  <li>use customization options</li>
</ol>

<p>See <a href="https://github.com/thecdil/bootstrap-template/blob/main/docs/create-website.md">docs/create-website.md</a> for details!</p>
